lans are  thoughtfully conceived  mindful of a wide array of tax legal and portfolio management considerations and  nimble enough to provide for flexibility in a constantly changing world   about us office history values and principles management team our founder  irving b harris contact us wealth management personal financial planning portfolio construction tax planning and preparation legacy and estate planning philanthropy risk management investments public equities fixed income alternatives real estate contact us william harris investors inc  n wacker drive suite  chicago il  phone   fax   infowilliamharrisinvestorscom  william harris investors inc  all rights reserved powered by backstop terms of use privacy policy risk management  william harris investors inc about   wealth management investments personal financial planning portfolio construction tax planning and preparation legacy and estate planning philanthropy risk management   will my family be ok without me are our longterm charitable objectives achievable what does the future hold for my family business how can i prepare for changes in the tax code after i am gone have we set aside enough money to cover the rising cost of education do i have enough life insurance am i getting sound tax advice are us treasuries as secure as they were how fragile is the us economy are my financial advisers trustworthy                     sleeping well at night what are the largest risks in my life is my family fully protected how should i invest my savings are my financial advisers savvy how does one protect against uncertainty are my assets sufficiently diversified how strong are my portfolio’s investment returns sleeping well at night             is my investment manager truly ’tax sensitive’ am i paying too much in fees is my asset allocation appropriate is my estate plan current do my heirs have enough money what will my legacy be will my heirs have too much money for how long can my family support its spending habits how long will i live will my healthcare plan provide properly for me how can i ensure that my heirs will be financially competent should something happen to me who will look after my family are my own spending and income assumptions realistic                               risk management     through the last five decades our clients have come to count upon us not only to provide them with a broad spectrum of financial and wealth services but also to shield them from harm today among our greatest responsibilities is that of anticipating and mitigating risk on behalf of our clients   risks come in all shapes and sizes many of these risks are relatively obvious and lend themselves to straightforward mitigation techniques some however are more veiled or complex and require more creative contingency planning   relatively obvious risks include permanent portfolio impairment the failure to implement and maintain a proper estate plan and exposure of personal assets to creditors less obvious risks may include health risks the trustworthiness of household help the robustness of one’s health insurance or the potential for identity theft still other risks may be mitigated significantly by preventive measures including educating our clients on many of the opportunities and responsibilities that accompany wealth   at whi we see it as our responsibility to assist our clients in identifying potential sources of risk and uncertainty and then in a disciplined thorough and methodical manner implementing a broad spectrum of risk mitigation measures to reduce their exposure to sources of potential liability   there are times when the best offense is a good defense precisely because so few things in life are certain we see it as among our greatest responsibilities to ensure that our clients are protected from unnecessary exposure to risk this page requires adobe flash to upload documents please click to download about us office history values and principles management team our founder  