r of financial and client services ms stephens is a certified public accountant with an ms in taxation from depaul university and a bs in accounting from st mary’s college at notre dame before joining whi she was with the public accounting firms of arthur young and then ernst  young for eight years she currently serves on the board of directors of giordano jazz dance chicago   michael mcquinn has been with whi since  and has been a vice president of whi since  he currently serves as director of taxes and trust administration mr mcquinn is a certified public accountant and has bs and ma degrees in accountancy from the university of illinois prior to joining whi mr mcquinn spent ten years with ernst  young where he worked as a senior manager in the tax practice group   marc bassewitz has been with whi since august  and is a vice president of the organization currently serving as general counsel and chief compliance officer prior to joining whi he was senior vice president general counsel and secretary of bally total fitness corporation mr bassewitz practiced law at latham  watkins llp as an associate and partner from  until  he received his ba and jd degrees from the university of michigan and is a past president of the board of directors of the juvenile diabetes research foundation illinois chapter   annmarie wolf has been with whi since april  and is a vice president of the organization serving as treasurer ms wolf is a certified public accountant and a certified management accountant she received an mba in finance from depaul university and a bs in accountancy from illinois state university prior to joining whi ms wolf spent eight years with harris associates lp working directly with alternative investments mutual funds and corporate accounting   duane dibble has been with whi since february  and is a vice president of the organization serving as the chief information officer prior to joining whi mr dibble spent twelve years at harris associates as manager of portf